WRITING.TEXT:
 yes, you can. I'm not sure why others have said you can't.

You would have routes like this:

 Route::get('/form', 'controller@get');

 Route::post('/form', 'Controller@post);

 Route::get('/sayhi/{name}, 'Controller@sayHi');

Your form page would post to /form and the post() function in that controller would end up doing this

 return redirect('/sayHi/'.$r-input('name'));

This may not be the best way to achieve what you're trying to do (you didn't really explain why it needed to be like this) but it's possible to do.
